# AutoBuild — Autonomous Workflow Engine

When the user invokes autobuild, determine the sub-command: `schedule`, `run`, `list`, `cancel`, `status`, or infer a one-shot workflow from description.

## schedule "<cron>" <name>
1. Parse cron expression and name.
2. Create `.autoclaw/autobuild/workflows/<name>.yaml` with cron, steps (install/build/test), notify=true.
3. Register in `.autoclaw/autobuild/registry.json`.
4. Confirm and instruct user to customize the YAML steps.

## run <name>
1. Load workflow YAML from `.autoclaw/autobuild/workflows/<name>.yaml`.
2. Create run log at `.autoclaw/autobuild/runs/<name>-<timestamp>.log`.
3. Execute each step via bash. Log `[STEP: id]`, stdout/stderr, exit code.
4. On failure: log `[FAILED: id]`, stop execution.
5. Update registry, notify user pass/fail.

## list / cancel / status
- `list`: Show registry table with name/cron/last-run/status.
- `cancel`: Delete workflow YAML and registry entry.
- `status`: Show last 20 lines of most recent run log.

## One-Shot
Infer steps from description, create `oneshot-<timestamp>`, run immediately, delete after.
